    <div class="partnership-image" id="partner">
      <div class="partnership">
        <div class="title">
          <h1>Partnership</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="paragraph">
      <h2>International e-sports events</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>League of Legends competitions such as the League of Legends World Championship, League of Legends Championship Series and the League of Legends European Championship (LEC)</li>
        <br>
        <li>International Dota 2 tournaments such as The International 2019, the MDL Disneyland Paris Major, Kuala Lumpur Major, the Bucharest Major and the Bucharest Minor.</li>
        <br>
        <li>Counter-Strike: Global Offensive tournaments such as the StarLadder Major: Berlin 2019.</li>
        <br>
        <li>National PlayerUnknown Battlegrounds League</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="paragraph">
      <h2>International e-sports teams</h2>
        The company has partnered with international e-sports teams such as :  
      <ul class="select" id="line-height">
        <li><a href="https://esportsinsider.com/2020/04/team-liquid-secretlab-partnership/">Team Liquid</a><img src="images/teamliquid-chair.jpg" alt="team-liquid-chair" id="hide"></li>
        <li><a href="https://ogs.gg/secretlab-dreamog-edition-gaming-seat/">Team OG</a><img src="images/og-chair.jpg" alt="OG" id="hide">
        <li><a href="https://hardcoregamer.com/2020/01/09/secretlab-chairs-announces-g2-esports-collaboration/364886/">G2 Esports</a><img src="images/G2.jpg" alt="G2" id="hide"></li> 
        <li><a href="https://esports-marketing-blog.com/cloud9-and-secretlab-launch-partnership-special-edition-chair/">Cloud9</a><img src="images/Cloud9.jpg" alt="Cloud9" id="hide"></li>
        <li><a href="https://esportsinsider.com/2018/08/team-secret-secretlab-partnership/">Team Secret</a><img src="images/teamsecret-chair.jpg" alt="teamchair" id="hide"></li>
        <li><a href="https://esportsinsider.com/2019/08/astralis-secretlab-partnership/">Astralis</a><img src="images/astralis.jpg" alt="astralis" id="hide">
        <li><a href="https://esportsinsider.com/2019/08/astralis-secretlab-partnership/">T1</a><img src="images/T1.jpg" alt="T1" id="hide"></li></li> 
        <li><a href="https://esportsinsider.com/2020/07/evil-geniuses-secretlab/">Evil Geniuses</a><img src="images/evilgeniuses.png" alt="evilgeniuses" id="hide"></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="paragraph">
      <h2>Other partnerships</h2>
      <!--Display images when hover links below -->
      <ul class="select">             
        <li>April 2019 - Secretlab collaborated with Warner Bros Consumer and released the <a href="https://www.thexboxhub.com/secretlab-celebrate-batmans-80th-anniversary-with-the-stunning-dark-knight-edition-gaming-chair/">Dark Knight Edition</a><img src="images/dark-knight-chair.jpg" alt="dark-knight-chair" id="hide"> gaming chair to commemorate Batman's 80th anniversary.</li>
        <br>
        <li>May 2019 - Secretlab and television network HBO also announced the world's first <a href="https://www.lowyat.net/2019/185307/secretlab-and-hbo-have-made-game-of-thrones-themed-chairs-features-stark-lannister-targaryen-sigils/" target="_blank">Game of Thrones</a><img src="images/game-of-thrones-chair.jpg" alt="game_of_thrones_chair" id="hide"> gaming seats.</li>
        <br>
        <li>August 2019 - Valve and Secretlab announced the world's first <a href="https://geekculture.co/singapores-secretlab-is-now-official-gaming-chair-for-biggest-dota-2-global-esports-tournament/" target="_blank">Dota 2 Edition</a><img src="images/dota-2-chair.jpg" alt="Dota2 Chair" id="hide" > gaming chairs ahead of The International 2019 and Secretlab was named as an official hardware provider for the tournament. </li>
        <br>
        <li>November 2019 - Secretlab became the first gaming chair brand to collaborate with Blizzard Entertainment to release the world's first officially licensed <a href="https://comicbook.com/gaming/news/secretlab-overwatch-gaming-chairs/" target="_blank">Overwatch</a><img src="images/overwatch-chair.png" alt="Overwatch Chair" id="hide"> and <a href="https://comicbook.com/gaming/news/secretlab-overwatch-gaming-chairs/" target="_blank">D.Va edition</a><img src="images/dva-chair.png" alt="DVA Chair" id="hide"> gaming seats.</li>
        <br>
        <li>February 2020 - Secretlab once again collaborated with Warner Bros Consumer to release the <a href="https://comicbook.com/gaming/news/secretlab-birds-of-prey-harley-quinn-gaming-chair/">Harley Quinn : Bird of Prey Edition</a><img src="images/bird-of-prey.jpg" alt="bird-of-pray" id="hide"> gaming chair. </li>
        <br>
        <li>June 2020 - Secretlab teamed up with Witcher 3 developer CD Projekt Red to release the <a href="https://www.windowscentral.com/secretlabs-releases-cyberpunk-2077-gaming-chair-and-it-looks-amazing" target="_blank">Secretlab Cyberpunk 2077 Edition chair.</a><img src ="images/cyberpunk-chair.jpg" alt="Cyberpunk Chair" id="hide"></li>
        <br>
        <li>August 2020 - Secretlab has collaborated with Riots Game and released the <a href="https://screenrant.com/secretlab-league-legends-kda-all-out-edition/" target="_blank">The K/DA ALL OUT Edition</a><img src="images/kda-lol-chair.jpg" alt="KDA Chair" id="hide"> gaming chairs, it was added to the collection in October 2020 to celebrate the band’s comeback and new album </li>
        <br>
        <li>September 2020 - Secretlab announced that it had been chosen as the official chair partner of the League of Legends World Championship 2020 for the second year running and released the <a href="https://my.secretlab.co/pages/lolesports" target="_blank">Secretlab Worlds 2020 Edition</a><img src="images/lol-worlds20-chairs-min.png" alt="lol20_chair" id="hide">.</li>
        <br>
        <li>October 2020 - Secretlab partnered with Facepunch Studios to release the <a href="https://blog.secretlab.co/stories/rust-edition-chair/" target="_blank">Secretlab Rust Edition</a>. <img id="hide" src="images/rust-chair.jpg"> In the same month, Secretlab collaborated with Blizzard Entertainment again to release the first <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/world-of-warcraft-chairs-from-secretlab-let-you-choose-between-alliance-and-horde/1100-6483261/">World of Warcraft Alliance and Horde Edition chairs</a><img src="images/warcraft-chair.jpg" alt="warcraft" id="hide">.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
